The paper focuses on the physical layer (PHY) of the IEEE 802.11p standard for vehicular communication, which involves wireless networking, information theory, multimedia systems, cryptography, and systems and control. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). However, the paper also discusses channel propagation and quality of transmission, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia systems (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper mentions security issues, which fall under cryptography (cs.CR), and the evaluation of network performance, which is related to systems and control (cs.SY).
